- Intent
Encapsulate a request as an object, thereby letting you parameterize clients with
different requests, queue or log requests, and support undoable operations.

Command is a behavioral design pattern that lets you turn a request into stand-alone object,
which can be used to parametrize objects with different requests, queue or log requests, and support undoable operations.


-Decouple what is done from who does it. (Decouple actors from actions)

-Decouple what was done from when was done. (Do & Undo)